<TITLE> 'Right to info law execution won't be easy' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 22 (bdnews24.com)It will not be easy to implement the right to information law, home minister Sahara Khatun said on Friday. "I am optimistic that media professionals as well as people from all walks of life will benefit greatly on successful implementation of the right to information Act-2000," she said at a discussion on the freedom of press and objectivity in journalism at the Press Institute in Bangladesh. "But the implementation process is not progressing smoothly as it will take some time to change the long- running practice." The vice-chancellor of Dhaka university AAMS Arefin Siddique and director general of state-run Bangladesh Television Kazi Abu Zafar Siddiqi also spoke. Siddique said, "The freedom of press does not allow whimsical act." "The real freedom of press lies in publishing news by maintaining objectivity and code of conduct," he said "Editorials and sub-editorials may be swayed by political ideology but they should never deviate from objectivity," Siddique also said Sometimes media outlets move away from objectivity either because of the influence of the owners or other interests, he added. bd
